Video_Title: One e-cigarette with nicotine leads to adrenaline changes in nonsmokers' hearts | UCLA Health
Description: a new ucla study found that healthy nonsmokers experienced increased adrenaline levels in their heart after one electronic cigarette (e-cigarette) with nicotine. the findings are published in journal of the american heart association, the open access journal of the american heart association/american stroke association.
